\( I = s \) = specific volume of liquid ammonia
\n\( P = \) specific heat of liquid ammonia

for temperatures above 32° F, I = \( \frac{C}{T^3} + 0.001756(\theta - 32) \)

Find \( s \) when \( \theta = 45° F. \)
31. If \( Q = \frac{T_b}{\frac{1}{s_p}-\frac{1}{s_a}} \), Q being the leakage of fluid past a well-fitting plug, find \( Q \).

32. The total amperage conductors per pole due to the three windings in a railway motor = \( 2C \sqrt{\frac{I}{\delta}} \).

Evaluate this integral.

33. For a viscous fluid flowing through a narrow cylindrical tube of radius \( r \), the quantity \( Q \) is given by the formula—\n\( Q = \frac{\mu\pi}{r^2}\frac{\Delta P}{L} \), where \( \mu \) is the coefficient of viscosity.
